{"name":"Scroll Writing","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To scribe a known spell onto a scroll, creating a single-use magical device at a cost of 500 gp + 100 gp per spell level. Materials may include the finest vellum, paper, or papyrus; a fresh quill; and sorcerer&rsquo;s ink, such as sepia. This involved process requires one week per spell level.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"necromancer","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251303706,"modifiedTime":1681579244829,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"FPmb0Zq3Jl5Xi02t","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Scroll Use","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To decipher and invoke scrolls with spells from the <strong>Necromancer Spell List</strong> (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <strong>Table 96</strong>), unless the scroll was created by an ecclesiastical sorcerer (one who casts cleric or druid spells).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"necromancer","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251242630,"modifiedTime":1681579244829,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"KQUnQbQXO7PjFZgg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Alchemy","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 29\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>To practice the sorcery-science of alchemy. Apprentice necromancers learn how to identify potions by taste alone; albeit the practice is not always safe. At 7th level, a necromancer may concoct potions with the assistance of an alchemist. By 11th level, the assistance of an alchemist is no longer required. For more information, refer to <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <em>alchemy</em>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"necromancer","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679250807770,"modifiedTime":1681579244828,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"MFeGgqLqMn4a0pJB","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Command Undead","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 68\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 3rd level, cause undead to submit and serve. Refer to the cleric class and <strong>Table 13</strong> for rules regarding <em>turn undead</em>, with special attention given to <em>evil command of undead</em>. At 3rd level, a necromancer has 1st-level <em>turning ability</em> (TA 1). Like the cleric, the necromancer must stand before the undead, within 30 feet, and speak boldly a malefic commandment, whilst displaying a holy symbol (or a necromantic symbol/glyph of death). All other rules and restrictions can be found at the cleric&rsquo;s aforementioned <em>turn undead</em> ability.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"necromancer 3","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.MFeGgqLqMn4a0pJB"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679250807770,"modifiedTime":1681579244829,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"rUtMOqdqQoxthJ8W","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Sorcery","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 68\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Necromancers cast spells that they memorize from arcane tomes; they also gain divine favour from d&aelig;mons, netherworldly beings, and ineffable powers. The number and levels of spells cast per day are charted on <strong>Table 36</strong>, though necromancers of high intelligence gain bonus spells cast per day (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>intelligence</em>). For example, a 4th-level necromancer with 13 intelligence can cast four level 1 spells and two level 2 spells per day.</p>\n<p>The necromancer begins with a spell book that contains three level 1 spells drawn from the <strong>Necromancer Spell List</strong> (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <strong>Table 96</strong>). Through personal research and unspeakable pacts, necromancers develop one new spell at each level gain; this spell is learnt automatically, with no need of a qualification roll, but it must be of a castable level (see <strong>Table 36</strong>).</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial no. of spells known: &times;3</li>\n<li>No. of spells gained per level: &times;1</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Additional spells may be learnt outside of level training, but the process is more arduous (see <strong>Chapter 7: Sorcery</strong>, <em>acquiring new spells</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"necromancer","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251346735,"modifiedTime":1681579244829,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"vS07DRrk6jNfBLXN","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Read Magic","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 30\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>The ability to decipher otherwise unintelligible magical inscriptions or symbols placed on weapons, armour, items, doors, walls, and other media by means of the <em>sorcerer's mark</em> spell or other like methods.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"necromancer","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679251200032,"modifiedTime":1681579244829,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"xiCvGgj3scwYEnuD","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
